# Dedicated upload allowlist for the library-site Cloud Build.
# Passed via `gcloud builds submit --ignore-file=.gcloudignore-library` so it
# does NOT disturb the shared root .gcloudignore (tailored for lupine-start).
#
# The library build needs exactly two things:
#   1. library-site/ itself (build scripts, SPA src, Dockerfile, nginx, cloudbuild)
#   2. the repo markdown corpus that scripts/catalog.js renders
#
# Strategy: ignore every top-level entry, then re-include only what is needed.
# Leading-slash patterns anchor to the repo root so nested files of a
# re-included directory come along automatically.

# Ignore all top-level entries by default.
/*

# 1. The build package.
!/library-site
/library-site/node_modules
/library-site/dist

# 2. The markdown corpus (sources referenced by scripts/catalog.js).
!/docs
!/README.md
!/CHANGELOG.md
!/GLOSSARY.md
!/lit-review.md

# DESIGN.md lives under lupine-start; pull in that one file, not the whole app.
!/lupine-start
/lupine-start/*
!/lupine-start/DESIGN.md

# Never upload VCS metadata.
.git/
